dplyr & dbplyr

library(dplyr)

Attaching package: dplyr

The following objects are masked from package:stats:

    filter, lag

The following objects are masked from package:base:

    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
library(dbplyr)

Attaching package: dbplyr

The following objects are masked from package:dplyr:

    ident, sql
flights <- tbl(con, in_schema("datawarehouse", "flight"))
flights
flights %>%
  tally()
object.size(flights)
8440 bytes
flights %>%
  group_by(month) %>%
  tally()

show_query()

flights %>%
  group_by(dest) %>%
  tally() %>%
  show_query()
<SQL>
SELECT "dest", COUNT(*) AS "n"
FROM datawarehouse.flight
GROUP BY "dest"
complex_example <- flights %>%
  filter(distance > 100) %>%
  group_by(uniquecarrier, dest, month) %>%
  tally() %>%
  filter(n > 10) %>%
  group_by(uniquecarrier, dest) %>%
  summarize(n_avg = mean(n, na.rm = T) %>% as.integer()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n_avg))
complex_example
complex_example %>% show_query()
<SQL>
SELECT "uniquecarrier", "dest", CAST(AVG("n") AS INTEGER) AS "n_avg"
FROM (SELECT "uniquecarrier", "dest", "month", COUNT(*) AS "n"
FROM (SELECT *
FROM datawarehouse.flight
WHERE ("distance" > 100.0)) "thtonscksp"
GROUP BY "uniquecarrier", "dest", "month") "mtfyomcrci"
WHERE ("n" > 10.0)
GROUP BY "uniquecarrier", "dest"
ORDER BY "n_avg" DESC

join tables

#airports <- tbl(con, "airports")
airports <- tbl(con, in_schema("datawarehouse", "airport"))
new_flights <- flights %>%
  left_join(airports, by = c("dest" = "airport"))
new_flights
new_flights %>%
  group_by(state) %>%
  tally() %>%
  arrange(desc(n))

collect()

by_location <- new_flights %>%
  group_by(dest, long, lat) %>%
  tally() %>%
  collect() %>%
  mutate(n = as.numeric(n))
by_location

plotting

library(ggplot2) 
by_location %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(x = long, y= lat, size = n, color = n), alpha = 0.5)

Direct insights

new_flights %>%
  group_by(dest, airportname) %>%
  tally() %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%  # desc() inside arrange() get the top counts
  head(10)

pull() command

top_names <- new_flights %>%
  group_by(dest) %>%
  tally() %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  head(10) %>% 
  collect() %>%
  pull("dest")
top_names
 [1] "ATL" "ORD" "DFW" "DEN" "LAX" "PHX" "IAH" "LAS" "DTW" "SFO"

Take advantage of dplyrs laziness

top_flights <- new_flights %>%
  filter(dest %in% top_names)

Use View() to preview some of the data in the familiar data viewer

top_flights %>%
  head(1000) %>%
  collect() %>%
  View("top_flights")

Easily transition from data manipulation to plotting, without needing to import the data

top_flights %>%
  group_by(month) %>%
  tally() %>%
  collect() %>%
  mutate(n = as.integer(n)) %>%
  ggplot() +
    geom_area(aes(x = month , y = n), fill = "blue", alpha = 0.5)

NA

Thanks to the tidyverse approach, an entirly new plot can be built by adding one single line, and the data is still summarized inside the database

top_flights %>%
  filter(distance > 2000) %>%  # Added 
  group_by(month) %>%
  tally() %>%
  collect() %>%
  mutate(n = as.integer(n)) %>%
  ggplot() +
    geom_area(aes(x = month , y = n), fill = "blue", alpha = 0.5)

NA

  group_by(dest) %>%
  tally()

  arrange(desc(n))
